</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,332,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the first record of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani. As" authorityYear="1850" box="[749,906,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphiximorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[749,906,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">Sphiximorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[982,1027,333,356]" name="Iran" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">Iran</collectingCountry>
and the third record of it from the Middle East region in addition to previous records from Transcaucasia for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Illiger in Rossi)" authorityName="Illiger in Rossi" authorityYear="1794" box="[1030,1385,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subsessilis">
<emphasis box="[1030,1044,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1062,1180,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">subsessilis</emphasis>
(Illiger 
<emphasis box="[1280,1302,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">in</emphasis>
Rossi)
</taxonomicName>
and Asiatic 
<collectingCountry box="[238,318,404,429]" name="Turkey" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">Turkey</collectingCountry>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Loew)" authorityName="Loew" box="[367,605,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphiximorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euprosopa">
<emphasis box="[367,381,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[396,513,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">euprosopa</emphasis>
(Loew)
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Peck" box="[620,744,404,429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" refString="Peck, L. V. (1988) Syrphidae. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Akademia Kiado, Budapest, pp. 11 - 230." type="book chapter" year="1988">Peck 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Van" box="[757,1024,404,429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" refString="Van Steenis, J., Ricarte, A., Vujic, A., Birtele, D. &amp; Speight, M. C. D. (2016) Revision of the West-Palaearctic species of the tribe Cerioidini (Diptera, Syrphidae). Zootaxa, 4196 (2), 151 - 209." type="journal article" year="2016">
<collectingRegion box="[757,801,405,428]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">Van</collectingRegion>
Steenis 
<emphasis box="[897,947,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1850" authorityName="Rondani. As" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphiximorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1169,1326,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">Sphiximorpha</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" refString="Rondani, C. (1850) Nota sexta pro dipterologia italic de nova specie generis Ceriae Fabricii. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 8, 211 - 214." type="journal article" year="1850">Rondani, 1850</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[221,338,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cerioidini">Cerioidini</taxonomicName>
) has eight valid species in the Palaearctic region (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang" box="[897,1132,439,464]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" refString="Yang, C. &amp; Cheng, X. (1998) Syrphidae. In: Xue, W. &amp; Chao, C. (Eds.), Flies of China. Uol. 1. Liaoning Science &amp; Technology Press, Shenyang, pp. 118 - 223. [1996]" type="journal article" year="1998">Yang &amp; Cheng 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Van" box="[1144,1405,439,464]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" refString="Van Steenis, J., Ricarte, A., Vujic, A., Birtele, D. &amp; Speight, M. C. D. (2016) Revision of the West-Palaearctic species of the tribe Cerioidini (Diptera, Syrphidae). Zootaxa, 4196 (2), 151 - 209." type="journal article" year="2016">
<collectingRegion box="[1144,1188,440,463]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">Van</collectingRegion>
Steenis 
<emphasis box="[1281,1329,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName box="[199,481,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphiximorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euprosopa">
<emphasis box="[199,481,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">Sphiximorpha euprosopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the most similar species to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gilasian &amp; Vujic" authorityName="Gilasian &amp; Vujić &amp; Hauser &amp; Parchami-Araghi" authorityYear="2017" box="[807,1122,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphiximorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ziegleri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[807,821,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[837,921,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">ziegleri</emphasis>
Gilasian &amp; Vujić
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1130,1228,476,501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1130,1222,476,501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
,
</emphasis>
has been reported only from Greece and Turkey (
<bibRefCitation author="Van" box="[516,795,511,536]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" refString="Van Steenis, J., Ricarte, A., Vujic, A., Birtele, D. &amp; Speight, M. C. D. (2016) Revision of the West-Palaearctic species of the tribe Cerioidini (Diptera, Syrphidae). Zootaxa, 4196 (2), 151 - 209." type="journal article" year="2016">
Van Steenis 
<emphasis box="[663,716,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). A male of 
<taxonomicName box="[948,1096,512,536]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphiximorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euprosopa">
<emphasis box="[948,962,512,535]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[979,1096,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">euprosopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Greece (Lesvos island, Sikaminia, 
<date box="[278,399,548,573]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" value="2001-04-24">24.iv.2001</date>
, leg. S. Rojo &amp; C. Pérez-Bañόn [FSUNS]) was re-examined during the course of the present study and compared with 
<taxonomicName authority="Gilasian &amp; Vujić &amp; Hauser &amp; Parchami-Araghi, 2017" authorityName="Gilasian &amp; Vujić &amp; Hauser &amp; Parchami-Araghi" authorityYear="2017" box="[443,555,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphiximorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ziegleri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[443,457,584,607]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[471,555,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">ziegleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[563,653,583,608]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[563,653,583,608]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
. Morphological differences between males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gilasian &amp; Vujić &amp; Hauser &amp; Parchami-Araghi, 2017" authorityName="Gilasian &amp; Vujić &amp; Hauser &amp; Parchami-Araghi" authorityYear="2017" box="[1178,1290,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphiximorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ziegleri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1178,1192,584,607]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1206,1290,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">ziegleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1298,1388,583,608]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1298,1388,583,608]" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and those of 
<taxonomicName box="[247,392,621,644]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphiximorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euprosopa">
<emphasis box="[247,261,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[275,392,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="40">euprosopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are listed in 
<tableCitation box="[537,623,620,645]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="13.[151,239,692,715]" captionText="TABLE 2. Morphological differences between males of Sphiximorpha ziegleri sp. nov. and Sphiximorpha euprosopa." pageId="13" pageNumber="40">Table 2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
